To resolve this issue, you need to update the `gulpfile.js` to use the ECMAScript Module (ESM) syntax for importing the `gulp-autoprefixer` module. Here's how you can do it:

1. Rename the `gulpfile.js` to `gulpfile.mjs` (or any other `.mjs` extension) to indicate that it is an ECMAScript Module.

2. Update the first line of the `gulpfile.mjs` to use the `import` statement instead of `require`:

```javascript
